<subSubSection pageId="37" pageNumber="38" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,511,151,210]" box="[151,441,186,210]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
(
<figureCitation box="[158,260,186,210]" captionStart="PLATE 5" captionStartId="45.[151,229,1946,1967]" captionTargetBox="[207,1388,163,1909]" captionTargetId="figure-65@45.[192,1403,151,1936]" captionTargetPageId="45" captionText="PLATE 5. A–G. General habitus. (A) Evansolidia inca, sp. nov.; (B) Evansolidia recurvata, sp. nov.; (C) Evansolidia unilamina, sp. nov.; (D) Evansolidia lyrata, sp. nov.; (E) Evansolidia fletcheri, sp. nov.; (F) Spinolidia moweri, sp. nov.; (G) Omanolidia inflata, sp. nov." pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Plate 5A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[271,433,186,210]" captionStart="FIGURES 275–282" captionStartId="82.[151,258,1921,1942]" captionTargetBox="[242,1349,212,1878]" captionTargetId="figure-70@82.[216,1371,191,1900]" captionTargetPageId="82" captionText="FIGURES 275–282. Evansolidia fletcheri, sp. nov. (275) male pygofer, lateral view; (276) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (277) right style, lateral view; (278) right style, dorsal view; (279) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (280) aedeagus, dorsal view; (281) dorsal connective, dorsal view; (282) connective, caudal view." pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Figs. 275–282</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1436,258,1038]" box="[151,624,258,283]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis box="[151,243,259,283]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,236,259,283]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Length</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Male 8.00 mm; female unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1436,258,1038]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,462,295,319]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" reason="1">External morphology.</emphasis>
General color of dorsum black with yellow to ivory markings; forewings with veins black, basal half of clavus ivory, 2 translucent broken transverse bands; mesonotum black with ivory markings on each of side of middle and lateral margins; pronotum black with irregular ivory transverse band on anterior margin, narrow ivory transverse band on posterior margin; crown black with longitudual yellow stripe medially and on lateral margins; eyes grey; clypeus and clypellus black with yellow longitudinal stripe medially, yellow stripe below each eye (
<figureCitation box="[262,365,474,498]" captionStart="PLATE 5" captionStartId="45.[151,229,1946,1967]" captionTargetBox="[207,1388,163,1909]" captionTargetId="figure-65@45.[192,1403,151,1936]" captionTargetPageId="45" captionText="PLATE 5. A–G. General habitus. (A) Evansolidia inca, sp. nov.; (B) Evansolidia recurvata, sp. nov.; (C) Evansolidia unilamina, sp. nov.; (D) Evansolidia lyrata, sp. nov.; (E) Evansolidia fletcheri, sp. nov.; (F) Spinolidia moweri, sp. nov.; (G) Omanolidia inflata, sp. nov." pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Plate 5A</figureCitation>
). Head narrower than pronotum, anterior margin obtusely rounded; crown narrower than width of eyes, lateral margins convergent basally; pronotum moderately large, shorter than crown; mesonotum large, about half as long as pronotum; forewings typical; clypeus elongate, lateral margins broadly convex; slightly excised near middle; clypellus short, about 1/3 as long as clypeus, inflated and broad basally, apex flared.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1436,258,1038]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,376,618,643]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" reason="1">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer in lateral view triangulate, small digitate lobe on caudodorsal margin (
<figureCitation box="[1266,1364,618,642]" captionStart="FIGURES 275–282" captionStartId="82.[151,258,1921,1942]" captionTargetBox="[242,1349,212,1878]" captionTargetId="figure-70@82.[216,1371,191,1900]" captionTargetPageId="82" captionText="FIGURES 275–282. Evansolidia fletcheri, sp. nov. (275) male pygofer, lateral view; (276) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (277) right style, lateral view; (278) right style, dorsal view; (279) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (280) aedeagus, dorsal view; (281) dorsal connective, dorsal view; (282) connective, caudal view." pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Fig. 275</figureCitation>
); right subgenital plate long, narrow, glabrous (
<figureCitation box="[601,700,654,678]" captionStart="FIGURES 275–282" captionStartId="82.[151,258,1921,1942]" captionTargetBox="[242,1349,212,1878]" captionTargetId="figure-70@82.[216,1371,191,1900]" captionTargetPageId="82" captionText="FIGURES 275–282. Evansolidia fletcheri, sp. nov. (275) male pygofer, lateral view; (276) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (277) right style, lateral view; (278) right style, dorsal view; (279) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (280) aedeagus, dorsal view; (281) dorsal connective, dorsal view; (282) connective, caudal view." pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Fig. 276</figureCitation>
); style shorter than aedeagus, broad, in lateral view broadly lobed on ectal margin, digitate apically (
<figureCitation box="[533,698,690,714]" captionStart="FIGURES 275–282" captionStartId="82.[151,258,1921,1942]" captionTargetBox="[242,1349,212,1878]" captionTargetId="figure-70@82.[216,1371,191,1900]" captionTargetPageId="82" captionText="FIGURES 275–282. Evansolidia fletcheri, sp. nov. (275) male pygofer, lateral view; (276) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (277) right style, lateral view; (278) right style, dorsal view; (279) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (280) aedeagus, dorsal view; (281) dorsal connective, dorsal view; (282) connective, caudal view." pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Figs. 277, 278</figureCitation>
); aedeagus in lateral view inflated medially, tubular throughout in dorsal view, setaceous medially and subapically (
<figureCitation box="[708,876,726,750]" captionStart="FIGURES 275–282" captionStartId="82.[151,258,1921,1942]" captionTargetBox="[242,1349,212,1878]" captionTargetId="figure-70@82.[216,1371,191,1900]" captionTargetPageId="82" captionText="FIGURES 275–282. Evansolidia fletcheri, sp. nov. (275) male pygofer, lateral view; (276) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (277) right style, lateral view; (278) right style, dorsal view; (279) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (280) aedeagus, dorsal view; (281) dorsal connective, dorsal view; (282) connective, caudal view." pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Figs. 279, 280</figureCitation>
); connective Y-shaped, stem very short, membranous on each side of longitudinal ridge (
<figureCitation box="[612,712,762,786]" captionStart="FIGURES 275–282" captionStartId="82.[151,258,1921,1942]" captionTargetBox="[242,1349,212,1878]" captionTargetId="figure-70@82.[216,1371,191,1900]" captionTargetPageId="82" captionText="FIGURES 275–282. Evansolidia fletcheri, sp. nov. (275) male pygofer, lateral view; (276) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (277) right style, lateral view; (278) right style, dorsal view; (279) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (280) aedeagus, dorsal view; (281) dorsal connective, dorsal view; (282) connective, caudal view." pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Fig. 281</figureCitation>
); dorsal connective long, strap shape, slightly expanded basally (
<figureCitation box="[159,258,798,822]" captionStart="FIGURES 275–282" captionStartId="82.[151,258,1921,1942]" captionTargetBox="[242,1349,212,1878]" captionTargetId="figure-70@82.[216,1371,191,1900]" captionTargetPageId="82" captionText="FIGURES 275–282. Evansolidia fletcheri, sp. nov. (275) male pygofer, lateral view; (276) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (277) right style, lateral view; (278) right style, dorsal view; (279) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (280) aedeagus, dorsal view; (281) dorsal connective, dorsal view; (282) connective, caudal view." pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Fig. 282</figureCitation>
), attached to base of aedeagal socle (
<figureCitation box="[671,769,798,822]" captionStart="FIGURES 275–282" captionStartId="82.[151,258,1921,1942]" captionTargetBox="[242,1349,212,1878]" captionTargetId="figure-70@82.[216,1371,191,1900]" captionTargetPageId="82" captionText="FIGURES 275–282. Evansolidia fletcheri, sp. nov. (275) male pygofer, lateral view; (276) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (277) right style, lateral view; (278) right style, dorsal view; (279) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (280) aedeagus, dorsal view; (281) dorsal connective, dorsal view; (282) connective, caudal view." pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Fig. 279</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
